 Web Shell Persistence and Detection
Objectives
By the end of this lab, students will be able to:

Understand web shell concepts and their role in persistence attacks
Deploy and identify different types of web shells in web environments
Create detection scripts using file-based and log-based analysis
Implement automated removal and quarantine procedures
Develop monitoring solutions for ongoing web shell detection
Prerequisites
Before starting this lab, students should have:

Basic Linux command line proficiency
Understanding of web server concepts (Apache/Nginx)
Familiarity with PHP syntax and web application structure
Basic Bash scripting knowledge
